        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Son of man shall be betrayed...  men.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " There is a reference to the preparation thus mercifully afforded to the twelve in the angel's address to the women at the sepulchre, \"Remember how he spake unto you when he was yet in Galilee\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 24:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Jesus reiterates the prediction continually in order to familiarize his followers with the unwelcome, the incredible, reality. But the Messiah's Passion, death, and resurrection were ideas that they could not at once receive; so impossible they seemed in the very nature of things, so contrary to all their hopes and expectations. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Shall be betrayed",
        "children": []
      },
